com.awirtz.util
Interface RingBufferWriter

public interface RingBufferWriter

An interface describing the callback write method. This is used by RingBuffer.writer(RingBufferWriter, int) to allow more efficient pipelining.

Author:
Aaron Meriwether

Method Detail

write

void write(byte[] byteArray,
           int offset,
           int length)
A callback method which RingBuffer will invoke. This method will be invoked zero, one, or two times as dictated by the RingBuffer logic in order to fulfill the RingBuffer.writer(RingBufferWriter, int) request.

Parameters:
byteArray - The internal byte array of the RingBuffer object which needs to be written to.
offset - The offset in the byte array at which to begin writing.
length - The number of bytes to write.
